headline: TSMC Q3 profit expected to soar 28% on AI spending boom
summary: TAIPEI (Reuters) -TSMC, the world's largest manufacturer of advanced artificial intelligence chips, is expected to post a 28% jump in third-quarter profit to a record due to the insatiable demand for AI infrastructure, though U.S. tariffs could impact its outlook.  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co, the world's No. 1 contract chipmaker and a key supplier to Nvidia and Apple, is forecast to report a net profit of T$415.4 billion ($13.55 billion) for the three months through September 30, according to an LSEG SmartEstimate compiled from 20 analysts.  TSMC has already flagged a market-forecast-beating rise in third-quarter revenue of 30%.

headline: Piper Sandler Raises Price Target on AMD (AMD) to $240 After Landmark OpenAI Deal
